<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JAN 92 / Appointments: Hopkins quits NIIDB
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tony Hopkins, chief executive of the Industrial Development Board, Northern
Ireland's main jobs promotion agency, is quitting after four years.
The announcement came as a surprise to business circles. A brief statement
issued by the Department of Economic Development confirmed that Hopkins had
been invited to take up a position in the private sector. As a permanent
secretary, Hopkins is one of the highest paid civil servants in the
province; his post carries a salary of over Pounds 60,000.
His resignation comes at a time of changes in direction for the organisation
as a result of the government's emphasis on competitiveness.
Government sources stressed that his departure was unrelated to recent
criticism of the IDB by Noel Stewart, senior partner of Coopers &amp; Lybrand
Deloitte. Stewart argued last week that the IDB did not have the calibre of
executives required to achieve the government's new competitive strategy. He
pointed out that it would take time to develop the skills required for such
a sophisticated plan and he criticised the IDB's overseas operations.
*****
Lesley Knox, head of institutional business at Kleinwort Benson Investment
Management, has become chairman of KLEINWORT BENSON INTERNATIONAL
INVESTMENT. Colin Bradbury, Juliet Cohn, Simon Fenton, Georgina Perceval
Maxwell and Richard Watt have been promoted to directors of KBII. Alastair
Begg of KBIM joins the KBII board as chief investment officer and Keith
Jecks, formerly president, becomes chief executive.
*****
LLOYDS BANK has promoted Michael Riding, previously head of bank relations
and money transmission services, to be general manager, commercial service.
Peter Jameson is business development director.
*****
Alan Rubenstein moves from Scottish Widows to become director and head of UK
Equities at BARCLAYS DE ZOETE WEDD INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT.
*****
Colin Matthews has been promoted to Bank of Scotland's divisional general
manager, UK banking - England.
*****
At ABBEY NATIONAL, Charles Toner is promoted to European director. His place
as operations director is taken by Ian Harley, formerly finance director
(retail operations). His place is taken by Graeme Johnston, formerly manager
corporate development. Geoffrey Osbaldeston is promoted to director of
commercial services and Paul Gardner-Bougaard becomes md of Cornerstone.
</TEXT>
