FT  24 JAN 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Crisps never tasted so good
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A MORE subtly flavoured potato crisp or tortilla chip could result from a
French process to coat continuously the flavouring on both sides of the
crisp or chip within a completely closed system.
After leaving the fryer the food items pass into a biturbine, where two
turbines rotate and isolate the chips. An integrated powder dispersion unit
and air injection system puffs the flavouring on to the chips.
Developed by EMT Process, of Cabries, the process ensures that the crisps
emerge ready for packing.
