taking a final decision, although discussions with Monktonhall Mineworkers
were continuing, with no scheduled completion date.
British Coal said just before Christmas that it would negotiate leasing the
colliery with Monktonhall Mineworkers, rejecting the bid from Caledonian
Mining, the privately owned mining equipment company. It did so on the
recommendation of the consultants Wardell Armstrong.
Mr Ben Mason, managing director of Caledonian, said it was still interested
in leasing the pit, the first British Coal has offered to lease.
