FT  24 JAN 92 / World News in Brief: Galling news
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sunbathers run twice the risk of developing gallstones than those who prefer
the shade, according to a Dutch medical study. Many gallstones contain a
polymer whose creation is triggered by ultraviolet light.
