The move appears to be part of a growing trend of alliances between US and
Japanese pharmaceutical companies.
The companies said they would explore areas of co-operation, including
giving Yamanouchi access to Roberts' development, marketing and sales
network in the US. Roberts may have access to Yamanouchi's manufacturing
facilities.
