FT  23 JAN 92 / International Company News: Heavy trade in Zale bonds
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AS A bankruptcy decision looms today for Zale Corporation, the largest
retail jeweller in the US, analysts reported volatile trading in the various
debt issues belonging to company and its subsidiaries.
The retail group faces an involuntary bankruptcy petition filed by
bondholders in early January. At midnight today, a 20-day response period
for Zale expires, and a court hearing has been scheduled for Friday morning.
The initial response of Zale to the filing was to suggest the bondholders'
move was 'unfortunate' and that it would prefer to achieve an out-of-court
reorganisation. Since then, analysts suggest, the company has sought to win
support among creditors for a restructuring that would involve a
'pre-packaged bankruptcy' - where the bankruptcy process is used briefly, to
implement technically a financial reorganisation.
But some observers still thought it likely that Zale would be forced to
accede to the Chapter 11 petition, and that a full bankruptcy process would
result.
