FT  23 JAN 92 / Parliament and Politics: Militant takes lesson from Labour -
Expulsions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MILITANT, the far-left grouping, has expelled two longstanding members,
including Mr Ted Grant, its founding theoretician, in a move ironically
echoing Labour's purge of Militant supporters.
The body accused Mr Grant and Mr Alan Woods of setting up a rival
organisation. 'This is a clear split from Militant,' it said.
The expulsions stem from Mr Grant's opposition to Militant's plans to
abandon Labour entryism and work outside the party.
Militant supporters recently launched Scottish Militant Labour - described
as a campaigning socialist organisation. An SML candidate, Mr Tommy
Sheridan, will contest the Glasgow Pollok seat held by Labour's Mr Jimmy
Dunnachie in the general election.
Militant will also advocate support for Mr Terry Fields, the Liverpool Broad
Green MP recently expelled by Labour, in his attempts to retain the seat on
an independent ticket.
Militant was at pains yesterday to emphasise that its two rebels had
effectively 'excluded themselves'. Their expulsion decision was made at an
editorial board meeting.
</TEXT>
