FT  23 JAN 92 / More BAe jobs expected to go
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ANOTHER round of job cuts is likely at the military aircraft division of
British Aerospace, which has already announced significant closures and job
cuts.
BAe confirmed yesterday that a further review of its Warton unit in
Lancashire - encompassing sites at Warton, Preston and Samlesbury - is under
way as 'part of the continuing review of the business situation'.
The company was responding to a press report that the loss of 2,500 design
and development jobs at the unit would be announced today. The Warton unit
is working on the Tornado, Hawk and European Fighter Aircraft (EFA)
programmes.
BAe announced more than a year ago that it was to cut 3,000 manufacturing
and manufacturing-related jobs at the Warton unit and closing the Preston
site, reducing employment at the unit to 11,000. Preston will close early
next year.
