<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PRESIDENT George Bush yesterday named Mr Andrew Card, deputy White House
chief of staff, as Transportation Secretary.
If confirmed by the Senate, he will succeed Mr Samuel Skinner, the new White
House chief of staff.
The departure of Mr Card opens the way for a shake-up of White House staff,
after a management review by a senior RJR Nabisco executive and friend of Mr
