director.
Recent reports suggest a chill between Mr Skinner and Mr Darman, with the
chief seeking ways to break the director's near stranglehold on domestic
policy.
Mr Card, a Massachusetts state legislator in 1974-1983, ran unsuccessfully
for the governorship of the New England state in 1982. He served in the
White House under President Reagan, and stepped up to the post of deputy
chief of staff in 1989.
