FT  23 JAN 92 / Appointments: People potential at Laura Ashley
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Jim Maxmin, the energetic American chief executive of Laura Ashley, is
continuing to make rapid headway in reshaping the company's image.
Yesterday he announced the appointment of Denise Lincoln, 40, as global
human resources director with effect from February 3. She becomes the first
woman since the late Laura Ashley to sit on the board of the fabrics and
fashion group. About 80 per cent of the company's staff are female.
