<TEXT>
PUTNAM, one of the biggest US mutual funds, has mounted a fresh campaign to
penetrate the European institutional and retail fund management industry.
The Boston-based subsidiary of Marsh &amp; McLennan yesterday announced the
appointment of a British unit trust expert, Mr Jonathan Custance Baker, to
the new London-based post of director of European business development.
Although Putnam has maintained a London investment office for some years,
