meantime, its business in the US has been booming, with worldwide assets up
23 per cent to Dollars 52bn during 1991. Putnam manages investments for 1.7m
individuals and more than 200 institutional investors globally.
Mr Custance Baker, 42, ran James Capel's unit trust business until six
months ago. Previously, he was the founding president of the GT group's
mutual funds operation in San Francisco. Until recently, he was on the
executive committee of the Unit Trust Association.
'Putnam wants to make sure it is doing things in a way that will achieve
long-term success rather than instant results,' he said.
