FT  23 JAN 92 / World Trade News: UK group nears deal on Kuwait base
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A BRITISH consortium has obtained a letter of intent from Kuwait for work
thought to be worth up to Pounds 200m to rebuild the country's main naval
base, writes David White.
However, Taylor Woodrow. the construction concern which heads the British
Kuwait Defence Group, said it was still unclear when a firm contract might
be signed.
Its principal partners in the consortium are Wimpey and the shipbuilding
company Vosper Thornycroft.
Taylor Woodrow and Wimpey were involved, along with Amec, in another
consortium which won a contract last September for reinstating production at
oil wells in northern Kuwait.
The letter of intent was announced yesterday by Mr Tom King, the UK defence
secretary, in Kuwait on the last leg of a Gulf tour.
